 <H1>Summary of SQL’s DDL</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>DDL supports creation of relations, views and indexes.  Tables can also be altered (by adding or dropping fields and ICs).
</H2>
</UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Views can be queried just like ordinary relations, but only limited forms of updates are allowed.
</H2>
</UL><UL>
<LI><H2>The GRANT / REVOKE commands for controlling privileges (ability to read or modify a relation), in conjunction with views, provide a powerful security and access control mechanism.</H2>
</UL></P>
